This section will explain how to delete particular column and record(row) from a table.

1. Delete particular column from table:
    To delete particular column table we have to use sql Data Definition Language statements.

    Syntax: alter table tableName drop columnName;

    Note:- If we want to drop multiple columns at a time then use (,) with columns names.

2. Delete record from a table:
    To delete particular record from a table we have to use Data Definition Language statements.

    Syntax: delete from tableName where primaryKey and value of table.
            delete from customers where cust_id =001;

    Note:- you can customize the condition based on your specific requirements to identify the records you want to remove
            in table.